<h1>Equivalent operations</h1>

<form>

<h2>Skupper CLI</h2>

<pre>
# Proposed
skupper service add-port orders 8080 --name api --protocol tcp
</pre>

<h2>Skupper YAML</h2>

<pre>
version: 1
site:
  name: storefront
  provided-services:
    - name: orders
      ports:
        - port: 8080
          name: api
          protocol: tcp

# skupper init -f site.yaml
</pre>

<h2>Skupper YAML embedded in a ConfigMap</h2>

<pre>
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: skupper-config
  namespace: storefront
data:
  version: 1
  site:
    name: storefront
    provided-services:
      - name: orders
        ports:
          - port: 8080
            name: api
            protocol: tcp

# kubectl apply -f site.yaml
</pre>

<h2>Kubernetes custom resource</h2>

<pre>
apiVersion: skupper.io/v1alpha1
kind: ProvidedService
metadata:
  name: orders
  namespace: storefront
spec:
  ports:
    - port: 8080
      name: api
      # Why no protocol here?

# kubectl apply -f resource.yaml
</pre>

